article.headline: Central Michigan 74, Eastern Michigan 68
article.story: YPSILANTI, Mich. (AP) -- Giordan Watson tied a career high with 30 points and Chris Kellermann added 10 Saturday to lead Central Michigan to a 74-68 victory over Eastern Michigan in the Mid-American Conference opener for both schools. It was the first MAC win for first-year Chippewas coach Ernie Zeigler. The victory snapped a five-game losing streak in conference openers for Central Michigan (6-7). Jesse Bunkley and Carlos Medlock each had 15 points for the Eagles (5-9), whose three-game winning streak ended. After Jordan Bitzer's 3-pointer gave Central Michigan a 40-29 lead at the start of the second half, Eastern Michigan scored 13 of the next 15 points to tie the game at 42. Bunkley keyed the run with three 3-pointers. The Chippewas responded with six straight points to build a 48-42 cushion with 12:40 to play. The Eagles rallied and went in front 51-48 on Nick Freer's 3-pointer with 9:55 left. Central Michigan retook the lead 60-59 on Eddie Spencer's two free throws with 3:33 remaining. Spencer later gave the Chippewas a seven-point edge with 61 seconds left. Eastern Michigan was held to just three field goals in the last 7:24. Neither team could gain full control in the first half. There had been seven lead changes and four ties by the time the half ended with Central Michigan leading 37-29.
